snippet: Mr. Castro used a question on immigration during the Democratic debate to mount an attack that others in the race have used to great success.
lead_paragraph: Julián Castro on Wednesday night criticized former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. over his record, using a question on immigration during the Democratic debate to mount an attack that others in the race have used to great success.

snippet: Mr. Biden, the front-runner, was confronted over his record on health care and criminal justice, and this time not just from Kamala Harris.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. delivered a steadfast defense of his moderate policies in the Democratic primary debate on Wednesday, striking back at a familiar adversary, Senator Kamala Harris, but facing intensifying attacks on his record from liberal rivals including Senator Cory Booker and Julián Castro, the former housing secretary.

snippet: In a contentious exchange during the last round of Democratic debates, Ms. Harris confronted Mr. Biden about having worked with segregationists in the Senate and discussed her personal history with busing. Here’s a refresher.
lead_paragraph: Perhaps no moment from the first Democratic debates in June was more dramatic than the tense exchange between former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Senator Kamala Harris of California. The two Democrats sparred on the issues of race, segregation and school busing.

snippet: The candidates along the wings went hard after the night’s leading candidates, Joe Biden and Kamala Harris.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Wednesday’s debate was barely underway when the attacks began on former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Senator Kamala Harris, and some of their Democratic rivals rarely let up.

snippet: They’ve handed Trump an easy win and yoked themselves to a genuine bigot.
lead_paragraph: When I first heard that President Trump had gone after the Rev. Al Sharpton — and that Mr. Sharpton had responded in kind — I must admit that I laughed. Are there two New York City hustlers who deserve one another more?
